Richard Branson , founder and chairman
of Virgin Group Ltd., talks about the European sovereign-debt 
crisis, climate concerns and the need for greater competition 
across all industries.  He speaks in  London  with Bloomberg Television's Maryam 
Nemazee. (Source: Bloomberg)  00:00 "Hopeful signs" on EU crisis; single currency
02:23 Carbon War Room; challenges; Virgin "empire"
05:16 Competition: "big anything is a curse."  Running time 05:58
 